<!--
    This Razor view file is for the Privacy Policy page of the Contract Monthly Claim System (CMCS).
    It outlines the privacy practices and policies to inform users about how their personal information is handled.
    Below is a brief overview of each section and its purpose:

    1. Page Title:
       - Sets the page title to "Privacy Policy".

    2. Introduction:
       - Provides a welcome message and states the commitment to protecting personal information in accordance with the Protection of Personal Information Act (POPIA) of South Africa.

    3. Information We Collect:
       - Lists the types of personal information collected from users.

    4. How We Use Your Information:
       - Describes the purposes for which the collected information is used.

    5. Information Sharing and Disclosure:
       - Explains the circumstances under which personal information may be shared with third parties.

    6. Data Security:
       - Details the measures taken to protect personal information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.

    7. Your Rights:
       - Outlines the rights users have under POPIA regarding their personal information.

    8. Retention of Information:
       - States the duration for which personal information is retained.

    9. Changes to This Policy:
       - Informs users that the privacy policy may be updated and how they will be notified of changes.

    10. Information Regulator:
        - Provides contact information for the Information Regulator of South Africa for lodging complaints.

    This structure ensures that users are well-informed about their privacy rights and how their personal information is managed by CMCS.
-->

@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="privacy-policy">
    <h1 class="privacy-title">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <section>
        <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>Welcome to the Contract Monthly Claim System (CMCS). We are committed to protecting your personal information and your right to privacy in accordance with the <a href="https://www.gov.za/documents/protection-personal-information-act" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Protection of Personal Information Act (POPIA)</a> of South Africa. This privacy policy describes how we collect, use, store, and protect your personal information.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We collect personal information that you provide directly to us, including but not limited to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Name and contact information</li>
            <li>Employment details</li>
            <li>Banking information for payment purposes</li>
            <li>Claim details and supporting documents</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use your personal information for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>To process and manage your claims</li>
            <li>To communicate with you about your claims and account</li>
            <li>To comply with legal and regulatory requirements</li>
            <li>To improve our services and user experience</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>4. Information Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
        <p>We do not sell your personal information. We may share your information with:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Authorised personnel involved in claim processing</li>
            <li>Third-party service providers who assist in our operations</li>
            <li>Legal and regulatory authorities when required by law</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
        <p>We implement appropriate technical and organisational measures to protect your personal information against unauthorised access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>Under POPIA, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Request access to your personal information</li>
            <li>Request correction of your personal information</li>
            <li>Request deletion of your personal information</li>
            <li>Object to the processing of your personal information</li>
            <li>Lodge a complaint with the Information Regulator</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>7. Retention of Information</h2>
        <p>We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this privacy policy, unless a longer retention period is required by law.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this privacy policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new policy on this page.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>9. Information Regulator</h2>
        <p>You have the right to lodge a complaint with the Information Regulator of South Africa:</p>
        <p>
            The Information Regulator (South Africa)<br>
            JD House, 27 Stiemens Street, Braamfontein, Johannesburg, 2001<br>
            <a href="mailto:PAIAComplaints@infoRegulator.org.za">PAIAComplaints@infoRegulator.org.za</a>
        </p>
    </section>
</div>